text: Fruit farmer: Grows and harvests fruits such as apples, oranges, and berries.
Vegetable farmer: Cultivates and harvests vegetables like carrots, potatoes, and lettuce.
Dairy farmer: Manages cows for milk production and processes dairy products.
Sheep farmer: Raises sheep for wool, meat, and other products.
Construction laborer: Performs physical tasks on construction sites, such as digging and carrying materials.
Bricklayer: Lays bricks, concrete blocks, and stones to build walls and structures.
Carpenter: Constructs, installs, and repairs wooden frameworks and structures.
Electrician: Installs, maintains, and repairs electrical systems in buildings and equipment.
Plumber: Installs and repairs water, gas, and drainage systems in homes and businesses.
Software developer: Designs, writes, and tests computer programs and applications.
Web developer: Builds and maintains websites and web applications.
Data analyst: Analyzes data to provide insights and support decision-making.
Accountant: Prepares and examines financial records, ensuring accuracy and compliance with regulations.
Auditor: Reviews financial statements and records to ensure compliance and detect fraud.
Teacher: Educates students in schools, colleges, or universities.
Teaching assistant: Supports teachers in classrooms by helping students and preparing materials.
Nurse: Provides medical care and support to patients in hospitals, clinics, or homes.
Paramedic: Responds to emergency medical situations and provides pre-hospital care.
Chef: Prepares and cooks meals in restaurants, hotels, or other food establishments.
Waiter: Serves food and drinks to customers in restaurants and cafes.
